decks.notes: The deck focuses on quickly deploying low-cost aggressive creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Soul-Scar Mage to deal damage early and often. Supporting cards like Stormchaser's Talent and Fiery Impulse help to push through damage and control the board. Riverpyre Verge and Boomerang Basics provide additional resource generation and tempo plays. The main goal is to apply pressure on the opponent, forcing them to react to threats while the deck maintains card advantage and board presence. The deck aims to win the game quickly before the opponent can stabilize or mount a strong defense.

This deck revolves around setting up Lotus Field to generate a large amount of mana quickly, allowing for explosive plays and combos. It focuses on ramping up resources with cards like Arboreal Grazer and Crumbling Vestige, before using Scapeshift to find key pieces like Thassa's Oracle or Lumra, Bellow of the Woods for the win. The deck also includes various utility lands and spells to control the board and protect the combo. The goal is to outpace opponents and execute a game-winning play before they can respond effectively.

The main concept of this UR Aggro deck is to quickly and aggressively hit the opponent with creatures like Monastery Swiftspear, Soul-Scar Mage, and Emberheart Challenger while also utilizing instant and sorcery spells like Burst Lightning, Reckless Rage, and Stock Up to clear the way or pump up your creatures. The deck aims to maintain pressure on the opponent and control the board with a mix of burn spells, cheap creatures, and card draw to keep the momentum going and finish off the game fast.

The main concept of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures and burn spells, putting pressure on them from the start of the game. It focuses on dealing damage quickly and efficiently, using cards like Monastery Swiftspear and Soul-Scar Mage to achieve this goal. The deck also utilizes spells like Reckless Rage and Monstrous Rage to control the board and keep the pressure on the opponent. Overall, the deck aims to win the game as fast as possible through a combination of creature aggression and direct damage spells.

The main concept of this deck is to utilize the aggressive nature of green creatures combined with devotion to green to overwhelm opponents quickly. By ramping up mana with cards like Nykthos, Shrine to Nyx and Elvish Mystic, the deck aims to play large threats like Cavalier of Thorns and Old-Growth Troll early on. The inclusion of cards like Storm the Festival and Kiora, Behemoth Beckoner provide additional synergy and card advantage to keep up the pressure on the opponent. With a focus on early aggression and powerful creatures, this deck aims to dominate the battlefield and secure a quick victory.

This Dimir Control deck focuses on controlling the opponent's board through removal spells, hand disruption, and card advantage. The deck aims to stall the game until it can establish a dominant position with its high-value threats and attrition-based game plan. The inclusion of the companion Yorion, Sky Nomad allows for additional value and consistency in the deck's strategy. By efficiently managing resources and disrupting the opponent's game plan, this deck looks to outlast opponents and secure victory through strategic decision-making and powerful late-game plays.

The deck focuses on control and removal, using a mix of creatures like Beza, the Bounding Spring and Sheoldred, the Apocalypse, along with spells like Fatal Push and Thoughtseize to maintain board control. The land base includes dual lands for flexibility and consistency. The win conditions are incremental advantage and attrition, with cards like Preacher of the Schism and Elspeth, Storm Slayer providing additional value. Overall, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while establishing a strong board presence to secure victory.

The main focus of this Selesnya Aggro deck is to quickly flood the board with efficient creatures like Archon of Emeria and Skyclave Apparition, using mana ramp from Elvish Mystic and Llanowar Elves. Thalia, Guardian of Thraben helps to slow down opponents, while Collected Company provides card advantage. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a mix of aggressive creatures and disruptive elements, such as Ouroboroid and Aven Interrupter. Elspeth, Storm Slayer can help to close out the game or provide additional board presence when needed.

This deck aims to overwhelm opponents with a fast and aggressive strategy using a combination of low-cost creatures like Llanowar Elves and Elvish Mystic, as well as powerful angels like Resplendent Angel and Righteous Valkyrie. The deck also includes mana acceleration tools like Temple Garden and Brushland to help ramp up to its higher-cost creatures quickly. With a focus on generating creature tokens and gaining life, the deck can quickly build a board presence and pressure opponents into making difficult decisions to keep up with its aggressive game plan.

The deck focuses on using control elements to disrupt the opponent while generating card advantage. It includes a variety of removal spells, hand disruption, and card draw. The inclusion of Yorion as a companion allows for additional value by flickering permanents. The deck aims to control the game through counterspells, removal, and card advantage to eventually overwhelm the opponent with powerful threats and win the game. The mana base is designed to support the deck's strategy by providing consistent access to the necessary colors of mana.

The deck focuses on controlling the game through counterspells, removal, and card draw. It aims to stabilize the board with board wipes like Supreme Verdict and Teferi, Hero of Dominaria, while managing opponent's threats with cards like Dovin's Veto. Card advantage is key with Consult the Star Charts and Meticulous Archive, allowing the player to dig for answers. The deck also utilizes powerful planeswalkers like Elspeth, Storm Slayer and Settle the Wreckage to control the battlefield. The mana base is designed to support the control strategy and ensure consistency in casting spells.

The main theme of this Dimir Control deck is to hinder the opponent's strategy while generating card advantage and maintaining board control. By using a combination of removal spells like Fatal Push and sweepers like Cryogen Relic, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The inclusion of Thoughtseize and Narset, Parter of Veils adds further disruption and card advantage. Yorion, Sky Nomad serves as a companion for additional value, while cards like Boomerang Basics and Clearwater Pathway provide versatility and tempo advantage. The deck aims to outvalue and outlast the opponent through a combination of control elements.

The main focus of this Selesnya Aggro deck is to quickly establish a board presence with efficient creatures like Archon of Emeria, Skyclave Apparition, and Thalia, Guardian of Thraben, while using mana acceleration from Elvish Mystic and Llanowar Elves. The deck also utilizes cards like Collected Company to generate card advantage and maintain pressure on the opponent. The inclusion of cards like Abandoned Air Temple, Boseiju, Who Endures, and Ouroboroid provide additional utility and resilience in different matchups, allowing the deck to adapt and overcome various obstacles.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly ramp up mana with powerful green creatures like Llanowar Elves and Old-Growth Troll, while also utilizing devotion to green with Nykthos, Shrine to Nyx. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive plays and finish the game quickly with big creatures like Polukranos Reborn and Cavalier of Thorns. The use of cards like Kiora, Behemoth Beckoner and Storm the Festival helps maintain card advantage and keep the pressure on the opponent. Overall, the deck focuses on fast mana generation and aggressive creature plays to secure victory.

The deck focuses on controlling the opponent's actions and maximizing card advantage through counterspells, removal, and card draw. Using Teferi, Hero of Dominaria and other tools, the deck tries to maintain board control and disrupt the opponent's strategy while slowly grinding out a win. With a high land count and various sources of card advantage, the deck aims to outlast the opponent and close out the game with powerful finishers like Supreme Verdict and Hullbreaker Horror. Yorion, Sky Nomad provides additional value by blinking permanents for extra card advantage.

The main focus of this deck is to quickly fill your graveyard with spells to bring back Arclight Phoenix and use aggressive spells to control the board and deal damage to your opponent. The deck includes card draw options to help find the necessary cards quickly and protect your creatures, as well as a mix of lands to ensure smooth mana curve. The goal is to overwhelm your opponent with repeated attacks from Arclight Phoenix and other creatures, while controlling the board with removal and counter spells.
